Booleans_key2: Aapne abhi tak 2 tarah ke data type padhe jo javascript mein use hote hain.
Booleans_key4: Aapne inko `variables` mein store karna bhi seekha.
Booleans_key5: yahan par *myName* ne ek number aur *myAge* ne ek `string` data-type hold kiya hua hai.
Booleans_key6: Javascript mein ek aur tarah ka data-type hota hai. jise hum *boolean* kehte hain. *boolean* data-type mein bas 2 hi values aa sakti hain : *`true`* ya *`false`*
Booleans_key8: yahan pe *amIOld* aur *amIFat* `variables` ne boolean values *`true`* and *`false`* hold kar rakha hai.
Booleans_key9: **Note**: Jo `variable` mein koi value assigned nahi hota hai, use Javascript *undefined* data-type de deti hai.
